<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.1//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml11/DTD/xhtml11.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
<title>CSS Test: page properties: border properties - margin box inherits from @page</title>
<link rel="author" title="Tom Clancy" href="mailto:tclancy@revenution.com"/>
<link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-page/#page-properties"/>
<meta name="flags" content="paged" />
<meta name="assert" content="Border properties defined in CSS2.1 apply to margin boxes."/>
<meta name="assert" content="Border properties defined in CSS2.1 apply to the page box."/>
<style type="text/css">
	@page {
		border-right: 6pt solid green;
		@left-top {
			margin-left: 0.5in;
			border-left: 6pt solid green;
			content: "";
		}
		@left-middle {
			margin-left: 0.5in;
			border-left: 6pt solid green;
			content: "";
		}
		@left-bottom {
			margin-left: 0.5in;
			border-left: 6pt solid green;
			content: "";
		}
	}
</style>
</head>
<body>
	<p>When printed, the bar on the left is the same size as the bar on the right.</p>
</body>
</html>